<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2016/06/07/spring-for-apache-kafka-1-0-release-candidate-1-available">Spring for Apache Kafka 1.0 Release Candidate 1 Available</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/2158ce6e7c048277890eb64458864c1c?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/artembilan">Artem Bilan</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2016-06-07 10:46:00.0">June 7, 2016</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2519" href="/blog/2016/06/07/spring-for-apache-kafka-1-0-release-candidate-1-available#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><div class="paragraph">
<p>On behalf of the Spring Integration and Spring Cloud Stream teams, I’m pleased to announce that the <code>spring-kafka</code> (Spring for Apache Kafka) Release Candidate for version <code>1.0</code> is now available.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The artifacts <code>org.springframework.kafka:spring-kafka:1.0.0.RC1</code> and <code>org.springframework.kafka:spring-kafka-test:1.0.0.RC1</code> are available in the <a href="https://repo.spring.io/milestone/">Milestone</a> repository.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First of all many thanks to everyone involved, to active community members, who provided feature requests and contributions. Special thanks to <a href="https://github.com/martindam">Martin Dam</a>, who spent a lot of time helping us with the <code>pause/resume</code> algorithm to handle slow listeners.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
